def: A wood of small growth; a thicket of brushwood. See Coppice.Near yonder copse where once the garden smiled. Goldsmith.
The obtaining of a curve similar to a pulse curve orsphygmogram by allowing the blood from a divided artery to strikeagainst a piece of paper.
Situated under, or on the ventral side of, the liver; --applied to the interlobular branches of the portal vein.
Capable of being expressed, squeezed out, shown, represented,or uttered.-- Express"i*bly,adv.
A noun suffix with a diminutive force; as in baronet, pocket,facet, floweret, latchet.
Having no temptation or motive; as, a temptationless sin. [R.]Hammond.
A kind of loose-fitting plaited jacket, having a loose belt.
